source_text:
§lCraftPresence - Sub-Commands:
 §rSyntax: §6/<cp|craftpresence> <command>

 §6§lreboot §r- Reboot RPC
 §6§lshutdown §r- Shut down RPC
 §6§lcompile §r- Test the output of a placeholder expression, via Starscript
 §6§lsearch §r- Search for valid placeholders available to use with Rich Presence
 §6§lreload §r- Reloads CraftPresence data based on settings
 §6§lrequest §r- View join request info
 §6§lexport §r- View export commands for mod data
 §6§lview §r- View a variety of display data
 §6§lhelp §r- Views this page
target_text:
クラフトプレゼンス - サブコマンド:
 §rシンタックス: §6/<cp|craftpresence> <コマンド>

 §6shutdown §r- RPCをシャットダウン
 §6compile §r- Starscriptを介してプレースホルダー式の出力をテスト
 §6search §r- リッチプレゼンスで使用可能な有効なプレースホルダーを検索
 §6リロード §r- 設定に基づいてクラフトプレゼンスデータを再読み込み
 §6request §r- 参加リクエスト情報を表示
 §6export §r- Modデータのエクスポートコマンドを表示
 §6view §r- さまざまな表示データを表示

source_text:
§lCraftPresence - View Sub-Commands:

 §6§lcurrentData §r- Shows your current RPC data, in text
 §6§lassets §r- Displays all asset icons available
 §6§ldimensions §r- Displays available dimension names
 §6§lbiomes §r- Displays available biome names
 §6§lservers §r- Displays available server addresses
 §6§lscreens §r- Displays available Gui names
 §6§litems §r- Displays available item names
 §6§lentities §r- Displays available entity names
 §6§lplaceholders §r- Displays available placeholders
Notes:\n - Placeholders must be surrounded by curly brackets ("{foo.bar}")
Allows CraftPresence to remove excess visual improvements from the Gui\n (Can improve gui performance in some areas)

Whether to allow duplicate Rich Presence Events to be sent when refreshing the display\n Notes:\n - This can cause better detection of unexpected disconnections at the cost of increased network traffic
Whether to allow the endpoint icon system (Used primarily alongside Dynamic Icons)
Whether to allow Placeholder Previews to be displayed in applicable tooltips throughout the Config Gui
Allows CraftPresence to change its display based on entity data\n Note the following:\n - Requires an option in a valid entity message list

Allows CraftPresence to change it's display based on the Gui you're in
 Note the following:
 - Requires an option in Gui messages
 - In some Minecraft versions, Guis must be opened once before configuring
Allows CraftPresence to change it's display based on the item you're holding\n Note the following:\n - Requires an option in item messages

The amount of tries to attempt auto-reconnecting to Discord, in the event of an unexpected disconnection\n Notes:\n - The time between reconnections increases after each failed attempt, as a result of exponential backoff
The endpoint URL to use for retrieving server icons\n Notes:\n - This endpoint is used for Scroll List Previews for non-base64 Server Icons and the "server.icon" placeholder, if not overriden
Reset this config to its default settings\nWarning: This will overwrite all changes made once saved!
Synchronize any live changes made from the local config file\nWarning: This will overwrite any changes made in here if unsaved!
Whether to register this Client as an application with discord\n(Warning: Can have compatibility and JVM Issues)
Default icon\n(Used in main menu, dimensions and servers)
Whether to reset the Starting Timestamp when the RPC is rebooted
Server Motd to default to, in the case of a null Motd\n(Also applies for direct connects)

This Configuration Gui was made from scratch by
 Jonathing, and will continue to be maintained by
 CDAGaming. A lot of effort went into making this
 custom Gui, so show him some support! Thanks.

 Feel free to learn from this Gui's code on
 the CraftPresence GitLab repository.
Party Privacy Level\n(Applies when Join Requests are enabled)
Message data to attach with this value
Toggles the display of Party Info\n(Applies when Game State is non-null)
